=Weizhi zong 唯識宗=
Yogācāra school of Chinese Buddhism
==Persons==
* [[玄奘]] (602–664)
* [[窺基]] (632–682)
==Literature and Translations==
===Monographs===
* Dan Lusthaus: Buddhist phenomenology : a philosophical investigation of Yogācāra Buddhism and the Ch'eng Wei-shih lun. London: Routledge, 2002. 
===Articles===
* Wing Tsit-chan: Buddhist Idealism: Hsüan-tsang of the Conciousness-Only School. In: A Source Book in Chinese Philosophy. New Jersey: Princeton University Press, 1963: 370-395.